reviews.review_text: A completist's tape The sound here is not great, and David's right that it gets better as it goes along.  Bertha is nearly unlistenable, but the rest goes down OK, though slightly muddy, and noticeably speedy (a half-step high).  There's a weird noise and a cut at the end of Truckin - maybe some of the jamming got cut off.  The Other One alone is still worth the download (although the ravenous Tiger doesn't quite come through) unless the soundboards suddenly become available again.  Just start your download from Bird Song and put all of Disk 2 with Disk 1.
Beautiful recording This music rocks my soul
